# Vercel AI SDK v6 + AI Gateway Integration Rules

## Stack

- **Server**: `ai` (v6) — `streamText`, `generateText`, `streamObject`,
  `generateObject`, `convertToModelMessages`.
- **Client**: `@ai-sdk/react` — `useChat`, `useCompletion`, `useObject`.
- **Provider routing**: **Vercel AI Gateway** via plain `"provider/model"`
  strings (e.g. `"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4"`, `"perplexity/sonar"`,
  `"openai/gpt-5-mini"`). The gateway resolves the provider, handles
  failover, and centralizes observability and billing.
- **Secret**: `process.env.AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY` (server-only). Set via Vercel
  env (Sensitive) — never `NEXT_PUBLIC_*`. Use the typed accessor
  `aiGatewayApiKey` from `@/server/lib/secrets` when reading in more than one
  place.

> Do **not** install or import provider-specific packages
> (`@ai-sdk/openai`, `@ai-sdk/anthropic`, `@ai-sdk/perplexity`, etc.) unless
> the user explicitly asks for direct provider wiring. The Gateway is the
> default.

---

## When to Use Vercel AI SDK in a Route Handler

### ✅ Use a Route Handler with `streamText` / `generateText` for

- **AI chat interfaces** with real-time streaming
- **Text generation** that streams to the browser
- **Structured output** (`generateObject` / `streamObject`) that the browser
  consumes
- **Tool calling** orchestrated within a single request

### Push to a queue / worker when

- Work consistently exceeds the Route Handler `maxDuration` budget
- Multi-step pipelines persist credits, write to DB, or fan out to other
  services — implement the pipeline in `src/server/handlers/**` and dispatch
  via Vercel Queues. Stream tokens only from the Route Handler.

For credits, DB writes, and webhooks see `architecture-decision-rules.mdc`.

